            <abstract>
                <p>Continuation of the journey by ship of Teklā, accompanied by <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/>, 
                    <persName ref="PRS3725Elizabet"/>, <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/> and <persName ref="PRS9036Suriel"/>.
                    <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/> decides to disembark in a town called Ṭawā. They meet the daughter of the governor, whom <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/>
                    blesses.
                    They return to the ship. After arriving in Alexandria, <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/> leads Teklā to the prison where ʾEsi is imprisoned, and 
                    reveals her identity to her. Mary explains why she anointed Teklā and appoints <persName ref="PRS9036Suriel"/> to be with Teklā and ʾEsi until they
                finish their struggle, and finally returns to heaven.</p>
